Is “microservice” too watered down to be a useful term?
text:
I've been searching for a clear consensus definition of microservices for 3+ years, and still have none, just gazillion pet definitions. Stored Procedures "count" under some candidate definitions but not others. Same with Linux piping.

Some emphasize technology, others emphasize org structure/management. "How to modularize properly" is an age old problem that involves many factors & tradeoffs, domain experience, and knowing Conway's Law. Can this vocabulary problem be cleaned up? I'm boggled, your turn...

Show HN: Next-gen spreadsheet GRID launches GPT-3 powered formula copilot
text:
Hi Hacker News, we are submitting again after getting some great feedback on our first post about GRID.

We at GRID (a spreadsheet SaaS based in Reykjavik, Iceland) just launched the 2.0 version of our product today.

GRID combines the power of spreadsheets and presentation/text editing software into one product. You can edit your spreadsheet, and create an interactive doc on top of it which is connected to the underlying spreadsheet data. In today's launch, we introduced our GPT-3 powered formula assistant that allows you to write out queries in natural language, and the assistant will suggest formulas, right there in the cell.

We would love to hear your thoughts and feedback.

Here's a video that shows what the formula assistant can do: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=UIfAnEvDCdo&t=15s

Check out this blog our founder wrote about the various ways GPT could be leveraged for spreadsheets: https://medium.grid.is/gpt-3-and-spreadsheets-4808acfda30d
